thread.title: Defensive player week (9/14): Sunnyvale's Tre Sterling
thread.title_full: Defensive player of the week (9/14): Sunnyvale's Tre Sterling | Dallas Morning News

author: Rhiannon Walker
title: Defensive player week (9/14): Sunnyvale's Tre Sterling
text:
Tre Sterling, Sunnyvale What he did? Tre Sterling scored four touchdowns -- three offensive and one defensive -- in Sunnyvale's 70-38 victory over Nevada Community on Friday night at Braves Field.
Who is he? A 6-0, 180-pound junior free safety.
The stats: 16 solo tackles, 6 assists 2 interceptions, 1 45-yard interception return for touchdown and 1 pass breakup.
He said it: "It feels really good. I have a good time scoring on defense and just to put my team in a position to win. It gives my offense a better chance not to be on the field more -- it gives them rest. It's fun for me. We were in a coverage where we were supposed to drop back, and I saw my receiver try to run a double move, and I made a break on the ball."
Coach said it: "He does have a good knack for the ball. He's actually now three straight games on defense. He had one called back last week, so he's doing something right back there, that's for sure." -- John Settle.
Did you know? He had 14 carries for 110 yards and three touchdowns in the victory. Sterling recorded 88 yards on four kickoff returns.
